      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Liane Saunders became Strategy Director and Strategic Programmes Coordinator at the Foreign and Commonwealth Office in May 2017.</p>

<p>She has previously served in diplomatic roles in the Near and Middle East. Her London roles include leading the <abbr title="Foreign and Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr>’s counter-proliferation work and running its Crisis Centre, as well as work on the Middle East during the Arab Spring.</p>

<p>She returned to the <abbr title="Foreign and Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr> after 5 years in the National Security Secretariat at the Cabinet Office.</p>

</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4085">
            <h1 id="strategy-director-and-strategic-programmes-coordinator">Strategy Director and Strategic Programmes Coordinator</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Director of Strategy and Strategic Programmes Coordinator is responsible for:</p>

<ul>
  <li>policy planning: providing challenge and alternative perspectives; engaging with external organisations and thinkers on foreign policy in the UK and overseas</li>
  <li>improving the policy capability of the <abbr title="Foreign and Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr>
</li>
  <li>helping to ensure <abbr title="Foreign and Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr> corporate and policy objectives are joined up, including by overseeing the deployment of staff from the Projects Task Force to priority issues</li>
  <li>delivering the <abbr title="Foreign and Commonwealth Office">FCO</abbr> Board’s ambition for a strategic portfolio approach to delivering foreign policy through programme</li>
</ul>

</div>
